.TH NXYTOOLS 1 "March 2026" "nmap-xyberpix" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
nxy\-banner, nxy\-dnsperm, nxy\-httpfuzz, nxy\-wsprobe \- small authorized\-use lab helpers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B nxy\-banner
.B \-\-authorized
.I HOST PORT
.RB [ \-\-connect\-timeout
.IR SEC ]
.RB [ \-\-read\-bytes
.IR N ]
.br
.B nxy\-dnsperm
.B \-\-authorized
.BI \-\-domain " DOMAIN"
.RB [ \-\-word\-file
.IR PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-max\-names
.IR N ]
.br
.B nxy\-httpfuzz
.B \-\-authorized
.I URL
.RB [ \-\-iterations
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-\-delay\-ms
.IR MS ]
.RB [ \-\-insecure ]
.br
.B nxy\-wsprobe
.B \-\-authorized
.I HOST PORT
.RI [ PATH ]
.RB [ \-\-tls ]
.RB [ \-\-insecure ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
These utilities complement
.BR nfuzz (1)
and
.BR ngit (1)\:
minimal TCP/HTTP/DNS probes with input validation and caps.
Each program refuses to run without
.B \-\-authorized
or environment variable
.BR NXY_AUTHORIZED=1 .
.PP
Run
.B \-\-help
per tool for limits (timeouts, max bytes, max iterations).
Full operator notes:
.B docs/NXYTOOLS.md
in the nmap\-xyberpix tree.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR nfuzz (1),
.BR ngit (1),
.BR nmap (1)
